Comment.Text: Then comes the feature extraction part. The signal is filtered in a large mu/beta [8 30] Hz range. The filtered signal is then splitted in blocks of 1 second every 16th second and the logarithmic band power is computed thanks to the two Simple DSP and the Signal Average boxes. The matrices can then be converted in feature vectors. note: depending on what frequency range reacts best for the subject, you may have to tune this part of the scenario note: whatever change you do on this scenario, don't forget to do the same on the classifier trainer scenario

Overview This scenario can be used online once the CSP spatial filter and the classifier is trained. note: the recorded files go to the folder where the scenario xml is located (${Player_ScenarioDirectory}/).
The CSP spatial filter produced in the previous scenario is used prior to the feature extraction.
